	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You cover the bottom half of a rod of glass with a piece of fur and speak a word of power. As the fur begins to smoke, you yank the rod out of the fur and point it with a whip-like motion, a streak of lightning roaring out of the end of the rod as you do so.</em></p><p><strong>[[/save dexterity]]{Dexterity Save}</strong></p><p>The lightning ignites flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried, which take [[/r 1d10]] fire damage every round until extinguished as an action.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 8d6 lightning]] damage.*</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d6 lightning]]{1d6} for each spell level above 3rd.</p><p dir=\"auto\" id=\"viewer-f6jmp9907\"><em>Some objects may be too large or flammable to be simply extinguished as an action, and will require creative solutions.</em></p>",
